4014.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">bgwalker/iStock Unreleased via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Dollar stores have been under significant pressure in the current economic climate, with Dollar Tree (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DLTR\" title=\"Dollar Tree, Inc.\">DLTR</a></span>) and Dollar General (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DG\" title=\"Dollar General Corporation\">DG</a>) vastly underperforming relative to Walmart (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WMT\" title=\"Walmart Inc.\">WMT</a>) and Costco (</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2162004014/image_2162004014.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4741419-sell-dollar-tree-stock-heading-into-q3-earnings", "pub_date": "2024-12-02 06:42:17"}, {"id": "4741418", "title": "Autodesk Q3: Strong Billing Growth Supporting Future Growth", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"BIM (Building Information Modeling) concept. 3D digital model-based process that provides architects, engineers, constructors, and owners with a comprehensive view of the building project.\" data-id=\"1464033476\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"640px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Parradee Kietsirikul/iStock via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>I <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4661864-autodesk-stock-billing-changes-affect-free-cash-flow-but-likely-temporary\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4661864-autodesk-stock-billing-changes-affect-free-cash-flow-but-likely-temporary\" target=\"_blank\">initiated</a> a 'Buy' rating on Autodesk (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ADSK\" title=\"Autodesk, Inc.\">ADSK</a></span>) in January 2024, highlighting the company's billing shift from multi-year contracts to annual subscriptions. Autodesk delivered 11% revenue growth with 28% growth in total billings in </p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1464033476/image_1464033476.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4741418-autodesk-q3-strong-billing-growth-supporting-future-growth", "pub_date": "2024-12-02 05:58:20"}, {"id": "4732497", "title": "Preferreds Weekly Review: Agency Mortgage REIT Results Support Preferreds", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Growing housing graph\" data-id=\"1771879591\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">J Studios</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Welcome to another installment of our Preferreds Market Weekly Review, where we discuss preferred stock and baby bond market activity from both the bottom-up, highlighting individual news and events, as well as top-down, providing an overview of the broader market. We also<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> try to add some historical context as well as relevant themes that look to be driving markets or that investors ought to be mindful of. This update covers the period through the fourth week of October.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Be sure to check out our other weekly updates covering the business development company (\"BDC\") as well as the closed-end fund (\"CEF\") markets for perspectives across the broader income space.</p> <h2 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Market Action</h2> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Preferreds were down around 1% on the week, along with most other income sectors. Rising Treasury yields have put pressure on the sector since the Fed cut the policy rate, causing the recent drop in preferreds yields to stall and partly reverse.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"><figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/27/30644215-17300725289700208.png\" alt=\"Systematic Income Preferreds Tool\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Systematic Income Preferreds Tool</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">However, unlike in previous instances of rising yields, the market views higher yields as a sign of a resilient economy which, this time around, pushed spreads lower. Preferreds credit spreads stand near their lowest point in the last 5 years.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"><figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/27/30644215-1730072546513739.png\" alt=\"Systematic Income Preferreds Tool\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Systematic Income Preferreds Tool</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <h2 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Market Themes</h2> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Agency mortgage REITs have started to report Q3 results. For preferreds shareholders there was much to like. Book value has been rising, leverage has been stable or falling while equity issuance has been coming at a healthy clip. All of this helps to derisk the preferreds by raising the equity / preferreds coverage ratio.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Our favored preferreds issuers in the sector DX, NLY, and AGNC in that order all have healthy levels of equity coverage.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"><figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/27/30644215-17300818247527616_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"720\" data-height=\"632\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/27/30644215-17300818247527616.png\" alt=\"Systematic Income Preferreds Tool\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Systematic Income Preferreds Tool</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">All but two Agency mREIT preferreds have a SOFR-based Fix/Float coupon structure and of these we continue to like DX.PR.C which is expected to move out to the highest coupon level due to its elevated spread over SOFR.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"><figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/27/30644215-17300820054748251.png\" alt=\"Systematic Income Preferreds Tool\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Systematic Income Preferreds Tool</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <h2 class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Market Commentary</h2> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">RiverNorth CEF (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OPP\" title=\"RiverNorth/DoubleLine Strategic Opportunity Fund, Inc.\">OPP</a>) has launched a non-transferrable rights offering. What\u2019s unusual about this rights offering is that it gives shareholders a right to buy common as well as preferred shares of the new preferred - the 6% 2029 maturity OPP.PR.C. OPP already has OPP.PR.A and OPP.PR.B trading with yields below 6% however these two are perpetual whereas OPP.PR.C will be a term preferred.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"><figure class=\"regular-img-figure paywall-full-content invisible\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/10/27/30644215-17300822657685797.png\" alt=\"Systematic Income Preferreds Tool\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>Systematic Income Preferreds Tool</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Shareholders will receive one right for each share held and 6 rights will be required to buy 2 new shares of the common stock and one share of OPP.PR.C. There will surely be a lot of OPP shareholders who don\u2019t know a whole lot about preferreds and who won\u2019t have a good sense of whether OPP.PR.C is good value or not.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">At a 6% coupon, it would be the highest-yielding OPP preferred and the term feature makes it pretty attractive as a short-duration asset. For reference, OPP has modest leverage and a decent-quality portfolio with a bunch of Treasuries, non-Agency mortgages, CLO Debt, BDC bonds etc. There is no debt ahead of the preferreds in the capital structure. A 2% spread pick-up over Treasuries is not super exciting but it can certainly work as a dry powder allocation.</p> <div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder paywall-full-content invisible\"></div> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Very likely OPP.PR.C will be sold hard by some CEF investors who don\u2019t understand it and, because duration is so short and liquidity is likely to be poor, even a small price drop will quickly boost the yield of the preferred. A $1 drop will add around 0.35% or so of yield to the preferred. Something to put on the watchlist.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1771879591/image_1771879591.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4732497-preferreds-weekly-review-agency-mortgage-reit-results-support-preferreds", "pub_date": "2024-11-03 09:52:29"}]}